item.title: Portforwarding
item.dc:creator: @lilob2000 lilob2000
item.description:
@lilob2000 wrote:

[quote=“zyle1992, post:23, topic:431507”][quote author=lilob2000 link=topic=534187.msg3906225#msg3906225 date=1328242725]

how could it of stopped working if, you said that it could see your service on canyouseeme.org?

NO it can’t see my service
My portfowarding was working fine for about a month and 1 day i get on to run my server and it says error connectiong to server so i was like okay let me change my no-ip.
Still didnt fix so i went on canyouseeme.org and it said it could not see it

Yes i did make my firewall to accept the port as i said i dndt change any settings from the time it worked.

If it says that it can’t see your service, then you haven’t forwarded correctly.

I have teamviewer if you want to come see i had many people check my settings and said it was correct

You just said that you checked and it can’t see your computer.

Yeah but how could i not have portfowarded correctly if it worked fine for a month then it just randomly stopped working.
[/quote]

Did you restart your router/computer in that time? Perhaps the changes were temporary, in which case you should forward again.[/quote]
Im not too sure i probably did. I just got a new router because i thought it was my old router that caused it. I did change my router main port from 8080 to 43594 which made canyouseeme.org see the port. But i cant connect my no-ips to it for some reason
